SIMPLE: scapulary
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scapulary
<hw>Scap"u*la*ry</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>scapulaire</ets>, LL.
<ets>scapularium</ets>, <ets>scapulare</ets>, fr. L. <ets>scapula</ets>
shoulder blade.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>A loose sleeveless vestment falling in front and behind, worn by
certain religious orders and devout persons.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The
name given to two pieces of cloth worn under the ordinary garb and over
the shoulders as an act of devotion.</def> <rj><au>Addis &
Arnold.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>A bandage passing over the
shoulder to support it, or to retain another bandage in place.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scapulary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scapulary
<hw>Scap"u*la*ry</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Same as <er>Scapular</er>,
<pos>a.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scapulary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Scapulary
<hw>Scap"u*la*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Same as 2d
and 3d <er>Scapular</er>.</def><-- But 3d Scapular is (R. C. Ch.), not
(Zool.)! PCP -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scapulet</ent>⟦br⟧
